I'll soon be in a similar situation. I'll need a new website and am currently creating a list of what I'd like for accessibility and data privacy (so no Google Analytics, etc.), and I'm trying to figure out how to use Signal as the default for video calls. Explaining all this to the customers will definitely be a lot of work, but I think it's worth it!
@user4 @user3 You can do it! And I'm happy to help you with my experiences.
Website: Check out @user5. It seems simple, looks good, and is open source. I will switch one of my websites to it before the next renewal.
Signal: Take a look at cal.com. It's an open-source calendar service with integrations that allow you to schedule video calls with Element Call, Jitsi, and so on. Signal is also supported, but I haven't tested yet whether it works for messaging or video calls.
I can recommend @user6. End-to-end encrypted, decentralized, open source.
